-- China to Spend $15 Million a Year on Domestic Potash Search, Xinhua Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-07T23:55:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/china-to-spend-15-million-a-year-on-domestic-potash-search-xinhua-says.html
China plans to spend 100 million yuan
($15 million) a year to explore for potash reserves in the
country in the next five years, the official Xinhua News Agency
reported, citing an unidentified official with China Geological
Survey.  The Ministry of Land and Resources invested 50 million yuan
this year to hunt for domestic potash reserves, Xinhua reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
